The paper deals with lower bounds for query complexity of testing properties of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. The paper also involves the study of random Boolean functions, which is a topic in discrete mathematics, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of algorithms for testing properties of Boolean functions, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of geometric properties of Boolean functions, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible sub-category.
